9:
A catfolk settlement. They're letting
us hide here for the moment.
17:
My name is Helga. You can relax, for
I'm on your side.
20:
I came to your rescue after the
catfolk chief reported that someone
was hunting a descendant of the
lionfolk.
28:
I have some passing knowledge. A
long time ago, the lionfolk were
banished after stealing Whitetail's
treasure, yes?
30:
They also wield a power that other
beastfolk don't have. I wonder... can
you use it as well?
34:
Well, it hardly matters at present.
You should focus on resting while
you can—
37:
Tch. They move fast for a band of
thugs.
42:
Search every corner of this
trash-laden filth.
46:
I see that Claw failed to mention
that they have numbers and they're
organized.
49:
I'll distract them while you hide here.
All right?
54:
Show us where you're hiding the
lionfolk brat! We know he's here!
64: So you really were here, eh?
103:
You... You monster! Stay away from
us!
106: I... I wasn't... I didn't mean to...
110:
I've dealt with the others, but we
can't stay here.
119:
Hmm, we should be downwind from
them now. That will buy us some
time.
122:
By the way, that was quite the move
back there. Was that your special
lionfolk ability?
134:
Everything was my fault. If I hadn't
been there, those villagers would've
never been in danger...
141:
My mom was right. I should've never
used my power...
145:
Let me ask you this—why did you
use it in the first place?
154:
In that case, I believe it's fine to use
your power however you see fit.
157:
Perhaps the outcome won't be what
you expected, but sometimes
fortune favors the bold.
160:
Come now, we must be off. Can you
run?
169:
...He's tougher than I expected. My
regular guys won't be enough.
171:
And here I thought my employer this
time would have their plan together.
174:
...I'm adding to our contract. Bring
the boy to me.
